The code is too distributed but calls to remote objects simply return an object of this form

```python
class Result(object):
    def __init__(self, x, y):
        self._x, self._y = x, y

    def get_x(self):
        return self._x
    def set_x(self, value):
        self._x = value
    x = property(fget=get_x, fset=set_x)

    def get_y(self):
        return self._y
    def set_y(self, value):
        self._y = value
    y = property(fget=get_y, fset=set_y)
```

which when serialized by serpent raises the exception after recursing to *x* or *y*. Anyway, I have closed the issue but thanks for any opinion you have about the possibility of avoiding any serialization specific methods to the above object.

