@ceridwen Modifying the recipe I gave to @alexmojaki, to use a closure instead of sticking attributes on the wrapped function, you can use:

```
def attach(value):
    def real_decorator(wrapped):
        attribute = do_something(value)

        @wrapt.decorator
        def _real_decorator(wrapped, instance, args, kwargs):
            # can access attribute here
            return wrapped(*args, **kwargs)

        return _real_decorator(wrapped)

    return real_decorator
```

I am having a further play with the recipe you link as believe there could well be a simpler way of doing it, although it may have a higher run time cost.

