Yes, the `doc` decorator is a generic one and you can set the description field (and yes thay appears as "Implementation notes" into swagger UI.
You can also simply override the docstring in your child class.

The `doc` signature is `doc('swagger-operation-identifier', **kwargs) but most of the time you can use dedicated decorator so a classic API endpoint will look like:
```python
@users_ns.route('', endpoint='users_generic')
class UserGenericResource(GenericResource):
    @users_ns.doc('create_user')
    @users_ns.expect(users_api_model)
    @users_ns.response(201, 'Object successfully created.')
    def post(self):
        '''A password may be supplied at this endpoint. It will be hashed'''
        return super().post()
```

