@akellehe Nice work so far!

I have a general concern that for high volume consumers there could be non-trivial overhead maintaining timers for every message received.

As implemented, this is going to track timeouts for all messages even if a message timeout handler _hasn't_ been provided.  Should we only track timeouts when a handler is provided?   If so, that means that `Message.is_in_flight()` needs to track state independent of message timeout events.

