I disagree with your second claim, since IMO there should be two operands. The first one is `r2`, and the second one is `r2, #0x2`, which is _r2 right shifted by 2_. In this case, I think the ARM assembly representation is really weird (why does it use a comma to separate `r2` and `#0x2`?), but there are indeed two operands, not three. Let me know what you think!

